In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. reports that he has issued an Executive Order imposing sanctions on foreign individuals involved in the global illicit drug trade. The President states that the trafficking of illicit drugs, including fentanyl and synthetic opioids, into the United States is causing the deaths of tens of thousands of Americans annually. He attributes drug cartels, transnational criminal organizations, and their facilitators as the primary sources of these drugs, which fuel the current opioid epidemic and drug-related violence. President Biden declares that international drug trafficking poses an unusual and extraordinary threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. As a response to this threat, he declares a national emergency and emphasizes the need to modernize and update the country's approach to drug trafficking. The article includes a copy of the Executive Order issued by President Biden.